-- China Mobile’s Li Says 6.5 Million Customers Downloaded Apps
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-17T02:40:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-17/china-mobile-s-li-says-6-5-million-customers-downloaded-apps-in-first-half.html
China Mobile Ltd. said 6.5 million
of its customers downloaded 25 million applications in the first
half of 2010. China Mobile Chief Executive Officer Li Yue made
the comments at the Mobile Asia Congress in Hong Kong today.  “With the voice market becoming more saturated, digital
services will be the source for high growth,” Li said. “Mobile
devices will be the most important devices for people to receive
information.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jonathan Annells at 
 jannells@bloomberg.net  